# Commit messages (soulstruct-blender)

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/). See `CONTRIBUTING.md`.

## Required format

```
<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary ≤72 chars>

Optional body: why and what changed, not a file dump.
```

## Types and scopes

| type | use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | new user-facing behavior (Stan's Tools, import/export) |
| `fix` | bug fixes |
| `docs` | markdown only |
| `test` | smoke tests, headless Blender scripts |
| `chore` | submodules, deps, tooling |
| `refactor` | behavior-preserving restructure |

Common **scopes:** `stan-tools`, `animation`, `flver`, `shaders`, `submodules`, `blender`, `havok`, `binder`

## Do not

- Sentence-case summaries (`Fix animation export`)
- Vague messages (`wip`, `updates`, `misc`)
- Double apostrophes in summaries (`Stan''s` → `stan-tools` scope instead)

## Submodule bumps

```
chore(submodules): bump soulstruct-havok for <one-line reason>
```

Parent repo only records the pointer; implementation detail belongs in the submodule commit.
